    "This means that the literature review is still a time-consuming task that requires manual involvement 2.",
    "Therefore, it is necessary to assist the literature review process by automatically extracting key information from scientific articles.",
    "The automation of key information extraction can be categorized into two classes: metadata extraction and key-insights extraction 3.",
    "Metadata extraction encompasses retrieving fundamental attributes from scientific articles, including title, author names, publication year, publishing entity, abstract, and other pertinent foundational details.",
    "Researchers and digital repositories use metadata to determine the relevance of specific articles to their fields of interest or to facilitate search and filtering tasks."
